<refentry version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:id="imregionalmax3" xml:lang="en" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
<refnamediv><refname>imregionalmax3</refname><refpurpose>Find regional-maximum plateaus in a 3-D volume.</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>out = imregionalmax3(volume)
out = imregionalmax3(volume, connectivity)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv>
<refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist>
<varlistentry><term>volume</term><listitem><para>Numeric 3-D scalar volume.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term>connectivity</term><listitem><para><literal>6</literal>, <literal>18</literal>, or <literal>26</literal>. Default is 26.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term>out</term><listitem><para>Boolean volume marking every voxel belonging to a regional-maximum plateau.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsection>
<refsection><title>Description</title><para>A connected equal-valued plateau is marked when none of its connected neighbors has a greater value. The complete plateau is returned, including flat peaks.</para></refsection>
<refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[
volume = zeros(31, 31, 15);
volume(7:13, 7:13, 5:8) = 4;
volume(19:24, 18:25, 8:12) = 7;
maxima = imregionalmax3(volume, 26);
imshow3d(maxima, "3d", 1, 5000);
]]></programlisting></refsection>
